rsions. I need to verify that carefully!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Simplifying code assertions**\\n\\nI'm looking at this code snippet. It counts headers in a loop and then asserts that the count is greater than zero. The static helper seems to contradict using assertions directly. Wait, can it use static import? If that's the case, it could work that way. I'll need to figure out the scope of the static import to see if that's a viable solution. Let's explore that further to clarify how that works!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eHHs1ApiSZeM6p19b3N3eCAR|fc_0386b2a2f60e97ee0169ffeebede3c819082672da3f4a0d8f2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-web/5.3.18/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_web/JettyClientHttpResponseTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        String line;\n        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null && !line.isEmpty()) {\n            // Read until the end of the HTTP request headers.\n        }\n", "newText": "        String line;\n        int headerCount = 0;\n        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null && !line.isEmpty()) {\n            headerCount++;\n        }\n        assertThat(headerCount).isGreaterThan(0);\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1678, "output": 1206, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40260, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778380460265, "responseId": "resp_0386b2a2f60e97ee0169ffeead00e48190862cb8a3a60ca9d1"}}
